-- Accused Marathon Bomber’s Friend Reaches Bail Deal With U.S.
-- B y   E r i k   L a r s o n
-- 2013-05-06T14:49:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-06/accused-marathon-bomber-s-friend-reaches-bail-deal-with-u-s-.html
Robel Phillipos, who is accused of
lying to investigators after the marathon bombing, has reached
an agreement on bail terms with federal prosecutors, according
to an announcement from the Boston U.S. Attorney’s Office.  The bail terms, which haven’t yet been approved by a judge,
would include $100,000 bond and home confinement, according to
an e-mailed statement from the U.S. Attorney’s Office. A hearing
is scheduled for today at 2 p.m. in Boston federal court.  To contact the reporter on this story:
